        "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modeling studies",
        "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior computational and experimental hemolysis studies spanning 2008-2022, consolidating power-law damage accumulation coefficients, turbulent stress thresholds, and exposure time models from 14 independent research groups. This node aggregates findings from Giersiepen et al., Heuser & Opitz, and the NHLBI-sponsored interlaboratory comparison, providing the theoretical basis for the Lagrangian hemolysis model parameterization used in the current CFD analysis. The breadth and depth of this synthesis lends it significant epistemic weight as a near-foundational reference."
